# Build System

This is a C++20 Windows project built with MSBuild (Visual Studio). Do NOT use CMake on Windows — CMakeLists.txt is for Linux/macOS only.

## Build Command

Use VS 2026 MSBuild. The exact command:

```
& "C:\Program Files\Microsoft Visual Studio\18\Enterprise\MSBuild\Current\Bin\MSBuild.exe" "e:\Projects\New\tunnerer\crust.vcxproj" /p:Configuration=Debug /p:Platform=x64 /m /verbosity:minimal
```

- Debug output: `build\bin\Debug\crust.exe`
- Release output: `build\bin\Release\tunneltanks.exe` (named differently)
- Build config is in `config\Build.Defaults.props` (controls OutDir, IntDir)

## Runtime Dependencies

Before running `crust.exe`, these must be in `build\bin\Debug\`:
- `nanogui.dll` — copy from `libs\nanogui\out\build\x64-Debug (default)\nanogui.dll`
- `glfw3.dll` — copy from `libs\nanogui\out\build\x64-Debug (default)\ext_build\glfw\src\glfw3.dll`
- `resources\fonts\broddmin_5x10.bmp` — copy from `resources\fonts\`

## Project Structure

- Toolset: v145 (VS 2026), SDK: 10.0.26100.0, Language: `/std:c++latest`
- Precompiled header: `src/pch.h` (created by `src/pch.cpp`)
- Unity build enabled (`EnableUnitySupport`)
- Warnings as errors (`/WX`, `/W4`) — all warnings must be fixed, not suppressed
- Preprocessor: `USE_SDL_GAMELIB`, `DEBUG_TRACE_LEVEL=5`, `NOMINMAX`

## Solution Projects (crust.sln)

| Project | Path | Type |
|---------|------|------|
| crust (main) | `crust.vcxproj` | Application |
| SDL2 | `libs\sdl2\VisualC\SDL\SDL.vcxproj` | Static lib |
| SDL2main | `libs\sdl2\VisualC\SDLmain\SDLmain.vcxproj` | Static lib |
| nanogui | `libs\nanogui\nanogui.vcxproj` | DLL (pre-built, CMake-generated — MSBuild rebuild fails) |
| ecs_test | `libs\ecs\untests\ecs_test.vcxproj` | Test executable |

The nanogui vcxproj has a broken custom build step referencing a non-existent absolute path. It can't be rebuilt via MSBuild — use the pre-built DLL.

## Git Submodules

| Submodule | Path | Remote |
|-----------|------|--------|
| ecs.hpp | `libs/ecs` | `https://github.com/DeirhX/ecs.hpp.git` (branch: main) |
| nanogui-sdl2 | `libs/nanogui` | `https://github.com/DeirhX/nanogui-sdl2.git` (branch: master) |

When modifying files inside submodules, commit inside the submodule first, then stage+commit the submodule reference in the parent repo. Push submodules before pushing the parent.

Submodules may need `git config --global --add safe.directory <path>` due to ownership mismatch.
